fields.name: Labrador Retriever
fields.description: The Labrador is friendly, energetic, and playful. It was bred as a sporting and hunting dog but is widely kept as a companion dog. It may also be trained as a guide or assistance dog, or for rescue or therapy work.

fields.name: German Shepherd
fields.description: A German breed of working dog of medium to large size

fields.name: Dachshund
fields.description: A short-legged, long-bodied, hound-type dog breed. The dog may be smooth-haired, wire-haired, or long-haired, with varied coloration.

fields.name: Boxer
fields.description: A medium to large, short-haired dog breed of mastiff-type, developed in Germany. The coat is smooth and tight-fitting; colors are fawn or brindled, with or without white markings.
